SIMPLE: isodiametric
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isodiametric
<hw>I`so*di`a*met"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + <ets>diametric</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Developed alike in the
directions of the several lateral axes; -- said of crystals of both the
tetragonal and hexagonal systems.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the several diameters
nearly equal; -- said of the cells of ordinary parenchyma.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isodimorphic</ent>⟦br⟧
